Other genes, such as MECR (a mitochondrial enzyme involved in fatty acid metabolism), RCC1 (a regulator of chromosome condensation involved in cell cycle regulation), and SRSF4 (a splicing factor involved in RNA processing), may also be implicated in IBS, although their connections to the disorder are less direct.
